Class ApplicantMenu

java.lang.Object
boundary.ApplicantMenu
Direct Known Subclasses:
HDBOfficerMenu
public class ApplicantMenu extends Object
The ApplicantMenu class provides the user interface for applicant users.

This boundary class:

  • Displays available BTO projects based on applicant eligibility
  • Manages the application creation and withdrawal process
  • Handles enquiry creation, viewing, and management
  • Generates booking receipts for successful applications
  • Supports password changes and other account operations

  • Constructor Details

    • ApplicantMenu

      public ApplicantMenu(Applicant applicant)

      Parameters:

  • Method Details

    • show

      public void show()
      Displays the main applicant menu and handles user selections.

      Provides options for:

      • Viewing available projects
      • Managing applications
      • Managing enquiries
      • Generating receipts
      • Changing passwords
      • Logging out

    • viewAvailableProjects

      protected void viewAvailableProjects()
      Displays a list of BTO projects available for the applicant.

      Filters projects based on:

      • Project visibility
      • Applicant eligibility (age, marital status)
      • Available flat types
      • Previous application status

      Provides sorting and filtering options for easier navigation.

    • viewProjectDetails

      protected void viewProjectDetails(BTOProject project)
      Displays detailed information about a specific BTO project.

      Shows:

      • Project name and neighborhood
      • Application period
      • Available units for eligible flat types

      Allows the applicant to apply for the project if eligible.

      Parameters:
      project - The BTO project to display details for

    • applyForProject

      protected void applyForProject(BTOProject project)
      Processes an application for a selected BTO project.

      Checks for existing applications, displays eligible flat types, and creates a new application after user confirmation.

      Parameters:
      project - The BTO project to apply for

    • viewMyApplication

      protected void viewMyApplication()
      Displays the applicant's current application details.

      Shows:

      • Project and flat type information
      • Application status and date
      • Assigned flat type (for booked applications)
      • Status-specific messages and options

      Allows the applicant to request withdrawal if the application is still active.

    • viewMyEnquiries

      protected void viewMyEnquiries()
      Displays a list of enquiries created by the applicant.

      Shows the project name, enquiry content, and any replies for each enquiry. Allows the applicant to select an enquiry for editing or deletion.

    • createNewEnquiry

      protected void createNewEnquiry()
      Creates a new enquiry about a BTO project.

      Displays a list of visible projects, allows the applicant to select one, and submit a question about the project.

    • changePassword

      protected void changePassword()
      Handles the password change process for the applicant.

      Validates that the new password:

      • Is at least 6 characters long
      • Contains at least one letter
      • Contains at least one number
      • Is different from the current password

    • generateReceipt

      protected void generateReceipt()
      Generates a receipt for a booked flat application.

      This method creates a detailed receipt for applicants who have successfully booked a flat. The receipt includes:

      • Applicant's personal information (name, NRIC, age, marital status)
      • Project details (name, location, flat type)
      • Booking information (date, status)

      The receipt is saved as a text file in the "output_applicant" directory with a filename that includes the applicant's NRIC and project name for easy identification.

      This method is only available for applications with BOOKED status.
